The course describes some aspects of family planning and pregnancy, delivery; fetal development in preparation for extrauterine life (e.q. development of fetal senses and learning abilities), neonatal behavior and development, fetal and neonatal diseases and prognosis; mother-infant bonding and attachment, breast milk composition, breastfeeding and councelling of parents.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim is to provide the students, also as parents-in-future, with broader information about pregnancy and delivery; development of fetal and neonatal capabilities, behavior and care; how pregnancy and delivery influence neonatal health and behavior; why and how to promote breastfeeding; how to support mother-infant attachment and bonding.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students will be able to understand human fetal and neonatal development, learn results of fetal, neonatal and childhood neurobiological research. They will be able to demonstrate knowledge of consequences of pregnancy and delivery to the fetal and neonatal behavior and health. They will know the benefits of breastfeeding and composition of breast milk to promote breastfeeding.
